(7, 'Food Truck Festival', 'Festival Goes Digital SeeMore Interactive Partners with Columbus Food Truck Festival', '', '1', '1', '', '<p><string>Columbus, OH â€“ Columbus, Ohio based SeeMore Interactive is excited to announce a partnership with the Columbus Food Truck Festival to make this year''s festival the first interactive event of its kind. Utilizing SeeMore''s mobile image recognition platform, guest at the two-day festival will be able to scan a range of festival graphics with the SeeMore Interactive App and immediately trigger a dynamic experience with their favorite food trucks, bands and sponsors.</string></p> \r\n<p>"We are thrilled to provide this interactive experience for all of the Columbus foodies out there," said Neal Applefeld, founder and CEO of SeeMore Interactive. Guests coming to the festival will be able to learn more about the trucks and their diverse menus, preview participating bands and gather great offers from the sponsors. "It''s a fun way to explore the things you love and share those experiences with your social network," added Kevin Fekete, Senior Business Development Manager. "And itâ€™s the first of many mobile engagement opportunities in development for our SeeMore Columbus campaign."</p>\r\n<p>SeeMore provides an exciting digital experience by adding a layer of image recognition and augmented reality to brand graphics, catalogs and now food trucks. Simply by scanning a printed image with the SeeMore Interactive app, consumers can unlock coupons, view videos, share items on social media and shop â€“ all via their smartphone or tablet.</p> \r\n<p>The 4th annual Columbus Food Truck Festival will be held Friday, August 15th and Saturday, August 16th at the Columbus Commons.</p><p> \r\n</p><p style="text-align: center;">###</p>\r\n<p><strong>About SeeMore Interactive, Inc.</strong></p><p>SeeMore Interactive helps retailers and organizations engage in powerful ways with consumers by creating a new and exciting level of product interaction. SeeMore integrates image recognition, recommendation engine and location-based technologies with augmented reality to turn everything viewed through a consumer''s smartphone or mobile device into a digital, interactive experience. SeeMoreâ€™s technology has been used by leading brands like WOW! Cable, Sprint and Charming Charlie. \r\n</p>\r\n<p>For more information, visit <a href="http://www.seemoreinteractive.com">www.seemoreinteractive.com</a> and <a href="http://www.columbusfoodtruckfest.com"> www.columbusfoodtruckfest.com</a></p>\r\n', '2014-07-30 00:00:00', '', ''),
(8, 'SeeMore Interactive Participates in Fall Expo 2014', 'Columbus, Ohio based SeeMore Interactive is excited to announce its participation at the Fall EXPO 2014, which was held at Sunnyvale, California.', '', '1', '1', '', '<p>Columbus, OH: Columbus, Ohio based SeeMore Interactive is excited to announce its participation at the Fall EXPO 2014, which was held at Sunnyvale, California. The EXPO is a quarterly pitch competition event which is organized by Plug and Play. Guests at the one-day event this year were able to get an interactive experience by utilizing SeeMore’s mobile image recognition platform. By scanning a range of interactive markers with the SeeMore Interactive App, a dynamic experience was immediately triggered for the users to see.</p> \r\n<p>The Fall EXPO was held on Thursday, 18th September, 2014 and its focus was on latest trends in technology. The event featured more than 40 startup pitches, corporate networking and panel discussions. Guests could meet with entrepreneurs who are bringing new and exciting solutions in the market. The event continued from 9.30 AM to 7 PM. SeeMore Interactive was one of the participants which showcased its awesome technology to the guests at this event.</p>\r\n<p>The marketing platform from SeeMore Interactive provides a more personalized brand engagement to shoppers equipped with mobile devices. With the SeeMore Interactive app, static items can be tuned into 3D presentations, shoppers can purchase products in real-time and can easily share within their social media network.</p> \r\n<p>Consumers can feel and experience products virtually by scanning labels, products, bar codes, retail displays and packaging in certain GPS locations with the help of the SeeMore Interactive app. With the help of location and vision-based technologies, the app turns products, which are viewed through mobile devices, into an animated, digital and interactive experience. </p>\r\n<p>Consumers can navigate through features and benefits of the products with the recommendation tool of the app. With integrated e-commerce feature, shoppers can purchase anytime as per their convenience. The social shopping feature helps in tracking products, get new offers and recommendations, unlock coupons and share their wish lists with friends and family.  They can also see what their friends are sharing in their wish lists.</p>\r\n<p>The SeeMore Interactive app works for different verticals which include retail, consumer goods, insurance, banking, telecom, automotive, non-profit and more. </p>\r\n<p>Guests coming to this Fall EXPO 2014 were able to get a clear demonstration of how the SeeMore Interactive app works and how it can change the shopping experience of the consumers completely by providing them with an intuitive experience throughout the purchase process. </p>\r\n<p><strong>About SeeMore Interactive, Inc.</strong></p>\r\n<p>SeeMore Interactive helps retailers and organizations engage in powerful ways with consumers by creating a new and exciting level of product interaction. SeeMore integrates recommendation engine, image recognition and location-based technologies with augmented reality to transform everything viewed through a consumer''s smartphone or mobile device into a digital, interactive experience. Leading brands like Charming Charlie, Sprint, Miramax, Alliance Data Systems and more has used SeeMore Interactive’s technology.</p>\r\n', '2014-09-19 00:00:00', '', '');
